    base:desc "Design and Definition Phase: Building control engineers model devices—sensors, actuators, controllers—directly within the BIM environment, embedding control logic via BIM annotations. Extraction and Transformation Phase: Using Model‑Driven Engineering (MDE) principles, the enriched BIM models are parsed to generate structured, semantically‑rich representations (e.g., IFC with custom extensions). Deployment Phase: The transformation layer automatically creates deployable DT artifacts (e.g., Docker containers, micro‑services) with minimal manual intervention, packaging device models and connectors. Runtime and Synchronization Phase: Real‑time data exchange protocols (e.g., MQTT or OPC UA) continuously synchronize state between physical building assets and their digital twins, while interactive visualization tools (e.g., WebGL dashboards) provide immersive monitoring interfaces. Extension and Governance Phase: The framework exposes standardized extension points that allow DT engineers to integrate custom services and analytics; versioned artifacts are managed through a modular architecture to support controlled evolution and lifecycle governance across design, deployment, operation, and decommissioning."
